BIBLEQ

This program provides a concordance function.  It takes a query
(invocation argument or on standard input) and prints the corresponding
Bible verse.  A query takes the form:

	<word(s)>

Words with embedded single quotes (indicating possessive tense) should
be quited from any shell interpretation.

Synopsis:

$ bibleq [<word(s)> ...] [-af <argfile>] [-w <cols>]
		[-ndb <ndbname>] [-vdb <vdbname>] [-V]

where:

<word(s)>	one or more words to form the lookup query
-ndb <ndbname>	the bible-book DB-name
-vdb <vdbname>	the bible-verse DB-name
-w <cols>	output column width
-V		print the program version on standard-error and then exit

